{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 15:10:21.735041", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission complete.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty device: router_dist_2_1\n- root cause: ospf_area_misconfiguration\n\nRecommended next actions (optional, not submitted):\n- On router_dist_2_1, move the network 10.2.1.0/24 into OSPF area 1 (change \"network 10.2.1.0/24 area 66\" to \"area 1\") and reload/apply OSPF config.\n- Verify OSPF adjacency with adjacent core router and ensure route to 10.2.1.0/24 is distributed.\n- Confirm DHCP reachability and that clients in 10.2.1.0/24 obtain leases.\n- Re-run reachability tests for host_2_1_*.\n\nIf you want, I can perform the verification steps or enumerate affected hosts next.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2372, "output_tokens": 190, "total_tokens": 2562, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
